# Azure Blob Storage & CDN Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` in your project root and fill in your Azure values.

```bash
# Azure Blob Storage Configuration
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME=thinkdavidportfolio
AZURE_STORAGE_CONTAINER_NAME=images
AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING=DefaultEndpointsProtocol=https;AccountName=thinkdavidportfolio;AccountKey=...;EndpointSuffix=core.windows.net
AZURE_CDN_HOSTNAME=thinkdavid-images.azureedge.net
AZURE_RESOURCE_GROUP=thinkdavid-portfolio
```

**IMPORTANT: Case-Sensitivity**
- All paths preserve exact case: `peopleOfSicily` (not `peopleofsicily`)
- Directory names match filesystem exactly
- CDN URLs generated with case-preserving paths
